What has been accomplished
1. Python & Node.js Backend Integration
Extracted and ported the core logic from the veriables/skills_gap_analysis GitHub repository into a class-based 
ResumeAnalyzer
.
Rewrote the existing Node.js server (
index.js
), completely removing the dependency on API keys (OpenAI / Gemini).
The pipeline is now 100% offline and free.
Node.js natively spawns the Python CLI scripts (
parse_cli.py
 and 
analyze_cli.py
) right out of the Backend/ folder to scan resumes and build roadmaps instantly using the GitHub model dictionary tokens.
2. Modern Frontend UI (
Frontend/index.html
, 
Frontend/style.css
, 
Frontend/script.js
)
Retained the exact positioning, structure, and logic flow of the original HTML while completely rewriting the aesthetics.
Added a premium, modern design featuring:
Dark-mode aesthetic with vivid gradients and glassmorphism elements (glass-panel effect).
Floating background abstract shapes to create a polished "wow" factor.
Smooth micro-animations (buttons expanding, spinners, fade-in rendering for API responses).
Clean API integration code within 
script.js
 directly connecting to http://localhost:5000.
3. Startup Script
Provided a convenient 
start.bat
 script in the root directory.
How to Test and Run
Because the Node.js server (
index.js
) was updated, please restart your Node.js process to pick up the changes.

In your terminal, stop the current node index.js and run it again.
Open your web browser and visit http://localhost:3000.
Try pasting a data science resume (or uploading a file like 
test.js
 did) into the forms and click Generate Analysis.
The UI will automatically query the node backend, which spans the python tokenizer, maps matches, and renders the roadmaps natively without hitting OpenAI!
